{"parse":{"title":"Tourist sign","pageid":34070203,"revid":849150104,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;border-color:#cdcdcd;margin:10px\" align=\"right\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td align=\"center\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Sign_for_the_Isle_of_Wight_Bus_Museum.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Sign for the Isle of Wight Bus Museum.JPG\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Sign_for_the_Isle_of_Wight_Bus_Museum.JPG/180px-Sign_for_the_Isle_of_Wight_Bus_Museum.JPG\" width=\"180\" height=\"135\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Sign_for_the_Isle_of_Wight_Bus_Museum.JPG/270px-Sign_for_the_Isle_of_Wight_Bus_Museum.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6b/Sign_for_the_Isle_of_Wight_Bus_Museum.JPG/360px-Sign_for_the_Isle_of_Wight_Bus_Museum.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"3072\" data-file-height=\"2304\" /></a>\n</td>\n<td align=\"center\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Xianning-tourist-attractions-road-sign-9734.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Xianning-tourist-attractions-road-sign-9734.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/70/Xianning-tourist-attractions-road-sign-9734.jpg/180px-Xianning-tourist-attractions-road-sign-9734.jpg\" width=\"180\" height=\"135\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/70/Xianning-tourist-attractions-road-sign-9734.jpg/270px-Xianning-tourist-attractions-road-sign-9734.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/70/Xianning-tourist-attractions-road-sign-9734.jpg/360px-Xianning-tourist-attractions-road-sign-9734.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1280\" data-file-height=\"960\" /></a>\n</td>\n<td align=\"center\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Efes_sign.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Efes sign.png\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Efes_sign.png/180px-Efes_sign.png\" width=\"180\" height=\"93\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Efes_sign.png/270px-Efes_sign.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Efes_sign.png/360px-Efes_sign.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1046\" data-file-height=\"538\" /></a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\"><small>Various tourist signs</small>\n</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<p>A <b>tourist sign</b>, often referred to as a <b>brown sign</b>, is a <a href=\"/wiki/Traffic_sign\" title=\"Traffic sign\">traffic sign</a> whose purpose is to direct visitors to tourist destinations,<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> such as <a href=\"/wiki/Historic_buildings\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Historic buildings\">historic buildings</a>, tourist regions, caravan or camp sites, picnic areas, sporting facilities or museums. By international convention brown signs with white lettering and white pictograms are often used for this purpose.\n</p><p>In the mid-1970s tourist signs were introduced in <a href=\"/wiki/France\" title=\"France\">France</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Since that time the idea of directing tourists to sights and attractions using a uniform type of signage has spread around the world. In Germany these tourist signs were first used in 1984. It is not clear which of the two signs, to the L\u00f6wensteiner Berge or to Burg Teck, was first erected there.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Usage\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Usage</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Design\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Design</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Criticism\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Criticism</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Usage\">Usage</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tourist_sign&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Usage\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Tourist signs have three main applications:\n</p>\n<ul><li>as information signs and signposts that point to important tourist destinations or places of interest in a specific area, such as within a village or a town;</li>\n<li>as standard signs  used to mark tourist or <a href=\"/wiki/Holiday_route\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Holiday route\">holiday routes</a> with special themes; or</li>\n<li>to herald the presence of nearby landscapes, towns and regions, usually on long-distance routes such as motorways.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Design\">Design</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tourist_sign&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Design\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:UTafel_A115_Teilung.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/UTafel_A115_Teilung.jpg/220px-UTafel_A115_Teilung.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"154\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/UTafel_A115_Teilung.jpg/330px-UTafel_A115_Teilung.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2d/UTafel_A115_Teilung.jpg/440px-UTafel_A115_Teilung.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1500\" data-file-height=\"1050\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:UTafel_A115_Teilung.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Information sign commemorating the <a href=\"/wiki/Division_of_Germany\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Division of Germany\">division of Germany</a></div></div></div>\n<p>In many countries the design and use of tourist signs is laid down in order to ensure a uniform appearance. In addition to their typically brown and white colours, they use <a href=\"/wiki/Sans_serif\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sans serif\">sans serif</a> fonts that are easy to read. In order to improve their usefulness for tourists dual languages may be used. The pictograms employed are designed to be simple and meaningful, and are not multi-coloured.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Criticism\">Criticism</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tourist_sign&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Criticism\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Critics complain that tourists signs contain too much information and distract motorists from concentrating on the road. The number of tourist signs continues to grow and less significant destinations are increasingly being signed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tourist_sign&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Road_sign\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Road sign\">Road sign</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiReader/Unterrichtungstafeln\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"de:Wikipedia:WikiReader/Unterrichtungstafeln\">Wikipedia:WikiReader/Unterrichtungstafeln</a> for a list of tourist signs in <a href=\"/wiki/Germany\" title=\"Germany\">Germany</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tourist_sign&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.highways.gov.uk/our-road-network/tourist-signs/\"><i>Tourist Signs (Brown Signs)</i></a> at www.highways.gov.uk. Accessed on 10 Aug 13.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.spiegel.de/auto/fahrkultur/0,1518,625855,00.html\"><i>Touri-Tafeln an der Autobahn</i> (\"Tourist Signs on the Motorway\")</a> dated 11 August 2006 at Spiegel-Online</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.kulturfahrt-deutschland.de/content/view/16/52/\"><i>Kritik</i></a> (\"Criticism\") at Kulturfahrt-Deutschland.de</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Tourist_sign&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table role=\"presentation\" class=\"mbox-small plainlinks sistersitebox\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"40\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/45px-Commons-logo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/59px-Commons-logo.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1024\" data-file-height=\"1376\" /></td>\n<td class=\"mbox-text plainlist\">Wikimedia Commons has media related to <i><b><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Tourist_road_signs\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"commons:Category:Tourist road signs\">Tourist road signs</a></b></i>.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.sicherestrassen.de/VKZKatalog/Kat386.htm\"><i>Zeichen 386 Touristischer Hinweis</i></a> (\"Sign 386 - Tourist Information\") - Tourist signs in the German Road Traffic Act) <span class=\"languageicon\">(in German)</span></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20120426052313/http://www.leo.tu-chemnitz.de/index.php?article_id=193\"><i>Die braun-wei\u00dfen Hinweisschilder an der Autobahn kennt jeder - ihre Sch\u00f6pfer nicht</i></a> (\"Everyone Knows The Brown and White Signs on the Autobahn...\") at www.leo.tu-chemnitz.de <span class=\"languageicon\">(in German)</span></li>\n